## Vulnerability

In handleRekey() at pkg/transport/http/handler_rekey.go lines 121-146, the rekey message signature verification has silent skip conditions:

```go
if len(req.RekeyMessageCBOR) > 0 {
    var rekeyMsgForVerify message.Message
    if cfencoding.Unmarshal(req.RekeyMessageCBOR, &rekeyMsgForVerify) == nil && len(rekeyMsgForVerify.Signature) > 0 {
        campfirePubKeyBytes, hexErr := hex.DecodeString(oldCampfireID)
        if hexErr == nil && len(campfirePubKeyBytes) == ed25519.PublicKeySize {
            // ... signature check
        }
    }
}
```

Three bypass paths:
1. If CBOR unmarshal fails, the block is skipped (CBOR blob proceeds to storage without signature check).
2. If the message has an empty/absent Signature field, the check is skipped.
3. If campfirePubKeyBytes length is not ed25519.PublicKeySize, skipped.

An attacker can craft a CBOR blob that fails to unmarshal cleanly but still stores (the second decode at line 304 uses a fresh Unmarshal call and only checks err, not sig).

## Severity

P1 — partial bypass: attacker cannot forge a valid signature, but can inject a rekey message with no signature if the CBOR is crafted to fail the first unmarshal but pass the second. The impact is limited to log pollution and fake rekey messages being stored — not key material compromise.

## Fix Required

Change the condition to reject (return 401) on any parse failure or missing signature when RekeyMessageCBOR is non-empty:

```go
if len(req.RekeyMessageCBOR) > 0 {
    var rekeyMsgForVerify message.Message
    if err := cfencoding.Unmarshal(req.RekeyMessageCBOR, &rekeyMsgForVerify); err != nil {
        http.Error(w, "invalid rekey message CBOR", http.StatusBadRequest)
        return
    }
    if len(rekeyMsgForVerify.Signature) == 0 {
        http.Error(w, "rekey message missing signature", http.StatusUnauthorized)
        return
    }
    campfirePubKeyBytes, hexErr := hex.DecodeString(oldCampfireID)
    if hexErr != nil || len(campfirePubKeyBytes) != ed25519.PublicKeySize {
        http.Error(w, "invalid campfire ID", http.StatusBadRequest)
        return
    }
    // ... verify sig, return 401 on failure
}
```

