## Issue

In cmd/cf/cmd/join.go, pollForKeyDelivery() uses a custom bytesEqual() function for the sender check:

```go
func bytesEqual(a, b []byte) bool {
    if len(a) != len(b) {
        return false
    }
    for i := range a {
        if a[i] != b[i] {
            return false
        }
    }
    return true
}
```

This is not constant-time. A timing attacker who can make many crafted key-delivery requests and observe response time could potentially learn bits of campfirePubKeyBytes.

## Severity

P2 — practical exploitability is low (requires many observations, campfire IDs are public, and Ed25519 public keys are 32 bytes), but best practice for all cryptographic comparisons is to use crypto/subtle.ConstantTimeCompare.

## Fix Required

Replace bytesEqual with hmac.Equal or crypto/subtle.ConstantTimeCompare:

```go
import "crypto/subtle"
if subtle.ConstantTimeCompare(msg.Sender, campfirePubKeyBytes) != 1 {
    continue
}
```

The custom bytesEqual function can be removed entirely.

